1 0 0 1 50 480 Tm (Why The Breakthrough Matters Conceptually) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 466 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 452 Tm (The custom GQA attention slicer did not change what the model was trying to draw. It ) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 438 Tm (changed how the attention calculation was executed so it fit the hardware.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 424 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 410 Tm (It preserved the math structure:) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 396 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 382 Tm (query heads remain query heads) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 368 Tm (key/value heads remain key/value heads) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 354 Tm (GQA sharing remains valid) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 340 Tm (query tokens are processed in chunks) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 326 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 312 Tm (That made the computation memory-feasible without breaking the model's attention logic.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 298 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 284 Tm (Final Summary) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 270 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 256 Tm (The breakthrough was:) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 242 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 228 Tm (1. Full DreamLite-base did not fit on 4 GB VRAM.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 214 Tm (2. Sequential CPU offload solved model residency.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 200 Tm (3. Generic attention slicing failed because DreamLite-base uses GQA.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 186 Tm (4. Custom query-token slicing respected GQA structure.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 172 Tm (5. This unlocked 1024x1024 DreamLite-base float32 generation on the 4 GB GPU.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 158 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 144 Tm (The intuitive model is:) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 130 Tm () Tj
ET
